3.title: Red
3.body:
You know Earthers are ready for change in their government. Some turmoil on the planet may just be the catalyst. Your people are walking a fine line, causing strife, but not trying to start a war. Making Earth and her leaders look bad could help the average citizen of the galaxy.

A contact within Tharsis steel tells you that the product is made with an untested, unproven method. They believe use of the steel in large scale projects will lead to failure. However, you have a lot invested in the company and don't want them to look bad. 

You are aware that in the 1950s, the Pleiadian aliens offered to assit with advanced technology and spiritual awakening if the nations of Earth would agree to a nuclear non-proliferation treaty. Humans refused to give up their nuclear arms, and the agreement fell through. You are concerned that contact with alien life might cause a deeper divide along economic lines and think that should remain hidden.

4.title: Orange
4.body:
Your business relies on Mars having good relations with Earth and other nations so you can continue to transport people and goods between them. War tends to disrupt production and travel, and would not be best for your business.

You have infultrated every labor union on Mars. Any construction work that occurs will be under your control. You can put people loyal to you in nearly any labor situation.

You helped to cover up the fact that early top-secret photographs from Martian rovers showed signs of previous habitation. Officials were worried humans would not want to colonize the planet if they knew there was existing life. You had already built your fleet of colony ships and could not turn back. It would not look good if this was discovered.

5.title: Yellow
5.body:
Your business relies on Mars having good relations with Earth and other nations so you can continue to transport people and goods between them. War tends to disrupt production and travel, and would not be best for your business.

You have infultrated every labor union on Mars. Any construction work that occurs will be under your control. You can put people loyal to you in nearly any labor situation.

You helped to cover up the fact that early top-secret photographs from Martian rovers showed signs of previous habitation. Officials were worried humans would not want to colonize the planet if they knew there was existing life. You had already built your fleet of colony ships and could not turn back. It would not look good if this was discovered.

6.title: Green
6.body:
You are a member of a reptilian race that has infultrated humanity since the begining of time. Your origins lie deep within Earth's surface.  However, you've broken away from those of your race still on Earth and a secret war ensues. You would like nothing more than to see planet Earth destroyed entirely to kill all your enemies and hide any evidence of your origins.

Your personal oracle has warned you that there is bad mojo occuring at the poles of Mars. It will be very bad for your corporation if the original plan to terraform the planet and to detonate nuclear weapons at the poles is allowed to occur. 

You are aware that alien life existed, and in fact still exists on Mars. An ancient humanoid race of Martians occupied the planet along with a symbiotic creature. Because you know all this, there you will able to tell the true story through art and entertainment, potentially leading to billions of credits.

7.title: Blue
7.body:
The majority of your wealth comes from military contracts. Your positioned to gain a lot of money if Mars ever goes to war with another nation or increases their military defense spending.

Ceres is a highly advanced technological society. You have strong ties to many of their top scientists. You are aware that the Cerian leader has expansionist goals and would love to control Mars and Earth. You are not necessarily against this idea because of the knowledge and technology it can bring.

You are aware that a secret group of scientists have detected a series of odd readings at the Martian poles. They've developed an experimental nuclear device that will likely open a door to another dimension. The device will never pass normal regulations and will have to be hidden as part of the terraforming process.

In the 1950s a cohort of secret astronauts left Earth on an alien ship. One of the, your grandfather, returned a few years later with fanatical stories. You know about the residents of the Zeta Reticuli star system are popularly referred to as The Grays. In fact, your cousin on Europa has been in contact with them.

function drawTurns()
  math.randomseed(os.time())
  -- If we want to use yield to wait/sleep in the waitFrames
  -- function we need to start a Coroutine. See:
  -- https://api.tabletopsimulator.com/base/#startluacoroutine
  startLuaCoroutine(Global, "drawTurnCoroutine")
end

function drawTurnCoroutine()
 local turn_deck = getObjectFromGUID(bag_guid)
 turn_deck.shuffle()
 local turn_cards = turn_deck.getObjects()
--print(#turn_cards)
 for i=1, #turn_cards do

     --print(i)
     local turn_card = turn_deck.takeObject()

     local card_position = positions[i]
     turn_card.setRotation({0.00, 180.00, 0.00})
     turn_card.setPositionSmooth(card_position)

     waitFrames(10)
 end
  return 1 -- otherwise scripting error
end

function waitFrames(frames)
  while frames > 0 do
    coroutine.yield(0)
    frames = frames - 1
  end
end

function count_cards()
    cabbage_count=0
    carrot_count=0
    lettuce_count=0
    onion_count=0
    pepper_count=0
    tomato_count=0
    score_count=0

     --( object, forward , right {left} )
    -- print(  round3(pos1.x) .. " / ".. round3(pos1.y) .. " / ".. round3(pos1.z ) )
    allobjects=getAllObjects()
    for _, object in pairs(allobjects) do
        if object.tag=="Card" or object.tag=="Deck" then
            if on_board(object) and object.tag=="Card" and object.is_face_down then
                vegetable_search( object.getDescription() )
            elseif on_board(object) and object.tag=="Deck" and object.is_face_down then
                cards=object.getObjects()
                for x=1, #cards do
                    -- print(cards[x].description )
                    vegetable_search( cards[x].description )
                end
            elseif on_board(object) and object.tag=="Card" and object.is_face_down == false then
                score_count = score_count + 1
            elseif on_board(object) and object.tag=="Deck" and object.is_face_down == false then
                cards = object.getObjects()
                score_count = score_count + #cards
            end
        end
    end
    update_count_buttons()

end


function on_board(object)
    --[[Lower left corner is 8, 10 , columns are at 10.7, 6.5, -2.5
    search radius =4 column 8.5, 0, -8.5 row 5, 1, -3
    ]]
    radius=4
    columlist={10.5, 6.5, 2.5 , -1.8, -6 , -10.2}
    rowlist={ 7,  5, 3, 1, -1, -3, -5}
    self_pos=self.getPosition()
    for c=1, #columlist do
        for r=1, #rowlist do
            targetposition=return_pos_offset(self, rowlist[r] , columlist[c])
            distance=findProximity(targetposition, object)
            -- print( round3( targetposition.x) .. " / ".. round3(targetposition.y) .. " / ".. round3(targetposition.z) )
            if distance < radius then
                return true
            end
        end
    end
    return false
end

function vegetable_search(description)
    if string.find(description, "Carrot") then
        carrot_count    = carrot_count+1
    elseif string.find(description, "Cabbage") then
        cabbage_count   = cabbage_count + 1
    elseif string.find(description, "Lettuce") then
        lettuce_count   = lettuce_count+1
    elseif string.find(description, "Onion") then
        onion_count     = onion_count + 1
    elseif string.find(description, "Pepper") then
        pepper_count    = pepper_count + 1
    elseif string.find(description, "Tomato") then
        tomato_count    = tomato_count +1
    end
end

function update_count_buttons()
    self.editButton({ index = 1, label = cabbage_count })
    self.editButton({ index = 2, label = carrot_count })
    self.editButton({ index = 3, label = lettuce_count })
    self.editButton({ index = 4, label = onion_count })
    self.editButton({ index = 5, label = pepper_count })
    self.editButton({ index = 6, label = tomato_count })
end

function add_subtract(_obj, _color, alt_click)
  mod = alt_click and -1 or 1
  new_value = math.min(math.max(value + mod, MIN_VALUE), MAX_VALUE)
  if value ~= new_value then
    value = new_value
    updateDisplay()
    updateSave()
  end
end

function updateDisplay()
  	self.editButton({index = 0, label = tostring(value)})
end

--------- Utility Scripts ---------
function findProximity(targetPos, object)
    local objectPos = object.getPosition()
    -- local xDistance = targetPos.x - objectPos.x
    -- local zDistance = targetPos.z - objectPos.z
    local xDistanceabs = math.abs(targetPos.x - objectPos.x)
    local zDistanceabs = math.abs(targetPos.z - objectPos.z)
    local distance = xDistanceabs^2 + zDistanceabs^2
    return math.sqrt(distance)
end

function return_pos_offset(object, forward , right)

    distance_F = forward
    pos_targetF = object.getTransformForward()
    distance_R = right
    pos_targetR = object.getTransformRight()

    pos_current = object.getPosition()
    pos = {
        x = pos_current.x + pos_targetF.x * distance_F + pos_targetR.x * distance_R,
        y = pos_current.y + pos_targetF.y * distance_F  + pos_targetR.y * distance_R,
        z = pos_current.z + pos_targetF.z * distance_F   + pos_targetR.z * distance_R
    }
    return pos
end

function round3(number)
    num3= math.floor(number * 100 ) / 100
    return num3
end

    local socObjects=socZone.getObjects()
    for _, object in pairs(socObjects) do
            if string.find(object.getDescription(), "Society") then
                side = object.getVar("side")
                bonus = object.getVar("bonus")

                if  side == "right" then
                    score_count_right = score_count_right + bonus
                elseif side == "left" then
                    score_count_left = score_count_left + bonus
                end
            end
    end
end

ObjectStates.LuaScript:
leftzone = 'c24db0'
rightzone = 'deb54f'
societyzone = '105072'

function onload()
    createBtns()
end

function createBtns()
    self.createButton({
        index=0, click_function = "count_sl", function_owner = self, label = "COUNT", position = {0,1,1}, rotation = {0,0,0}, scale = {1,1,1}, width = 400, height = 400, font_size = 100, color = {0,0,0,1}, font_color = {1,1,1,25},
        tooltip        = update_tooltip,
    })

    buttonparama={
        index=1, click_function = "nulButton", function_owner = self, label = "00" ,position = {-.5,.6,0}, rotation = {0,0,0}, scale = {1,1,1}, width = 0, height = 0, font_size = 400, color = {0.5,0.5,0.5,0.5}, font_color = {128,0,0,25},
    }
    self.createButton(buttonparama) --1 score

    buttonparama.label="00"
    buttonparama.position={.5,.6,0}
    buttonparama.font_color = {139,69,19,25}
    self.createButton(buttonparama) --2 carrot
end

function nulButton()
end

function count_sl()
--{-14.20, 1.34, 10.92}  (society 1 card)

score_count_right = 0
score_count_left = 0


    societybonus = getSocietyBonus()
    count_cards(leftzone, "left")
    self.editButton({ index = 1, label = score_count_left })

    count_cards(rightzone, "right")
    self.editButton({ index = 2, label = score_count_right })
end


function count_cards(zoneguid, bonus)
    Tech_Zone = getObjectFromGUID(zoneguid)
    allobjects=Tech_Zone.getObjects()
    for _, object in pairs(allobjects) do
            if string.find(object.getDescription(), "Storyline") then
                realm_bonus = object.getVar(bonus)
            end
    end
 doMaths(bonus)

end

function doMaths(bonus) --need to make score different based on side
    for _, object in pairs(allobjects) do
        if  object.tag=="Card" and object.is_face_down == false and object.getVar('realm') ~= nil  then
            if bonus == "right" then
                score_count_right = score_count_right + object.getVar('value')
                decalTable = object.getDecals()
                if decalTable ~= nil then
                    score_count_right = score_count_right + #decalTable
                end
            else if bonus=="left" then
                score_count_left = score_count_left + object.getVar('value')
                decalTable = object.getDecals()
                if decalTable ~= nil then
                    score_count_right = score_count_left + #decalTable
                end

            end
        end
        if object.getVar("realm") == realm_bonus then
            if  bonus == "right" then
                score_count_right = score_count_right + 1
            elseif bonus == "left" then
                score_count_left = score_count_left + 1
            end

        end
    end
end
end

function getSocietyBonus()
    local socZone= getObjectFromGUID(societyzone)
    local socObjects=socZone.getObjects()
    for _, object in pairs(socObjects) do
            if string.find(object.getDescription(), "Society") then
                side = object.getVar("side")
                bonus = object.getVar("bonus")

                if  side == "right" then
                    score_count_right = score_count_right + bonus
                elseif side == "left" then
                    score_count_left = score_count_left + bonus
                end
            end
    end
end

ObjectStates.Name: go_game_piece_black
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
function onload()
    createBtns()
end
function createBtns()
    self.createButton({
        index=0, click_function = "cancelSociety", function_owner = self, label = "Flip", position = {0,.2,0}, rotation = {0,180,0}, scale = {1,1,1}, width = 400, height = 400, font_size = 100, color = {0,0,0,1}, font_color = {1,1,1,25},
        tooltip        = 'Flip Society 1 card'
    })

end

function nulButton()
end

function cancelSociety()
    cancels = getSociety()
    checkCancels("a4384c",cancels)
    checkCancels("0a57d1",cancels)
end


function getSociety()
    Tech_Zone = getObjectFromGUID('c00cf2')
    allobjects=Tech_Zone.getObjects()
    for _, object in pairs(allobjects) do
        if string.find(object.getDescription(), "Society") then
        cancels = object.getTable('cancels')
            if object.is_face_down then
                object.flip()
            end
        end
    end
    return cancels
end


function checkCancels(zoneguid, cancels)
    local Card_Zone = getObjectFromGUID(zoneguid)
    local zoneobjects=Card_Zone.getObjects()
    for _, object in pairs(zoneobjects) do
            if object.getVar('realm') then
                for index, value in pairs(cancels) do
                    if value == object.getVar('realm') and object.is_face_down == false  then
                        object.flip()
                    end
                end
            end
    end
end
